Mobiles.LongDescription: `aa fuzzy grey skitterer zips across the floor here.``
Mobiles.Description: `aA hairy grey skitterer bustles around here going about its business.  ```aIt is carrying a small amount of food to help feed it's larger kid.  ```aIt bears the mark of the arachnid queen and follows only her wishes.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `fa purple skitterer with `owhite spots `fstopped here to clean itself.``
Mobiles.Description: `fA purple skitterer with `owhite spots `fsits here minding his ```fown business and cleaningitself.  It's fangs are stained green and ```fdripping with poison.  It bears the mark of the arachnid queen.``

`bA large red and purple Arachnid stand before you here.  It's```bspider-likebody supports a very short, upright insectisoid torso ```btopped by a spider's head and long, sharp fangs.  It's front two```blegs act more like arms, with the remaining six legs supporting the```babdomen.  This particular Arachnid is a tunneler, and can use it's```bvery sharp claws to break off rocks from the tunnel walls.  The ```bArachnid bears the mark of the arachnid queen on its back, a ```bgolden-brown spider with a green gem in the middle of the torso```bbranded on it's back.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `iAn arachnid sapper is attempting to remove rubble.``
Mobiles.Description: `iA large blood red Arachnid stands here, a sack load of explosives```istrapped over it's back.  It's spider-likebody supports a very ```ishort, upright insectisoid torso topped by a spider's head and ```ilong, sharp fangs.  It's front two legs act more like arms, with ```ithe remaining six legs supporting the abdomen.  This particular```iArachnid is a sapper and it's using it's extensive knowledge of```iexplosives to attempt to remove rubble from caved-in passageways.```iThe Arachnid bears the mark of the arachnid queen on its back, a ```igolden-brown spider with a green gem in the middle of the torso```ibranded on it's back.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `jA bloated and mutated abomination roars at you threateningly.``
Mobiles.Description: `jWhat was once mostly likely a Vro'ath peasant now towers over you,```jit's skin bloated and tinted a bright green, an unpleasant mix of```jblood and neon green mucus dripping from it's even gaping jaw.  The```jmonsterous thing turns to look at you, with a look in it's twisted```jeyes that either say 'Yum, fresh meat' or 'Please kill me.'``

`aYou can tell from the development level of this particular spider```athat is seems to be no more than a younger spiderling of a giant```aarachnid race the Anarachadium seem to have an affinity for, however```athis particular spiderling is bloated and tinted a sickly greyish-```agreen, it is significantly larger than it should be and certainly```alooks more deadly.``

`fThis enlarged spiderling is bloated from draconic expirementation. ```fThe purple carapace sports green spots at the points where the ```fbloating seems to be concentrated.  This particular spiderling zips```faround the cave passageways, somewhat oblivious to it's own morphing```fbody.  The spiderling is picking up debris, discarded body parts, and```foccasionally gathers food to brind to its Anarachadium masters.``

`dThis larger Anarachadium represents the lowest level of the Arachnid```dalchemist caste.  The tiny torso that juts up from the spidery abdomen```dhas all sorts of leather slings tossed over it, holing all sorts of ```dcrude vials, herbs, and tinctures.  This particular Arachnid is ```dscurrying around the lab performing tests of all sorts on other spiders```dor even humanoids.  The Botanist bears the mark of the arachnid queen on```dit's back, a golden-brown spider with a green gem in the middle of the ```dtorso branded on it's back.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `iAn Arachnid `hExcavator `iis trying to clear the passageway``
Mobiles.Description: `iThis excavator arachnid is hacking away at piles of rubble with pick-axes```iin both arms, desperately trying to re-establish connection with the hive```iand allow his brother's in arms to breech through to the surface.  The ```iExcavator bears the mark of the arachnid queen on it's back, a golden-brown```ispider with a green gem in the middle of the torse branded on top of the ```iabdomen.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `dA once burly lumberjack, now tortured by disease lies here.``
Mobiles.Description: `dThe pale face of this lumberjack once sported a long, full beard.  However```dnow his face is patching and loosing hair.  All of his teeth are missing```dfrom his mouth.  His body is twisted and tortured by posion and disease,```dhe prays for some sort of escape from his plight.  ``

`gA large arachnid with painted symbols across his carapace and legs stands```gbefore you.  The arachnid is easily identified as a physician, across his```gshort torse are various slings and pounches that are stuff with herbs and```gvarious spell components to assist in the healing process.  The physician```gbears the mark of the arachnid queen on it's back, a golden-brown spider```gwith a green gem in the middle of the torso branded on top of the abdomen.``

Rooms.RoomDescription: `fA small crack of light peeks around the rock shoved aside at the ```fentrance of the cave.  The cave walls are jagged and etched with what ```flook like tool marks.  There is enough room for a few people to stand ```fin the entrance, and the cave seems to widen as it goes further down ```finto the earth.  The walls and floor or moist and the breeze coming in ```fthrough the crack pushes the stale, moist air passed your nose.  Little ```fspiderlings skitter along the floors and walls, spiders of all sizes ```fand shades of red, black and purple.  From deeper within the cave you ```fcan hear the echoes of scraping and even what sounds like tools chipping ```fagainst rock.``

Rooms.ExitMsg: `a$n heads $T and melts into the darkness.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: `fAs you progress further down the cave it becomes almost impossible to ```fsee much farther than a few meters in front of your face, no matter your ```fsource of illumination.  Now there seem to be small spiders everywhere, ```fit's almost impossible to avoid stepping on at least a few.  The sounds ```fof tools and loud scraping on the cave walls gets even louder.  ``

Rooms.ExitMsg: `a$n heads $T and melts into the darkness.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: `fThe sound of digging is even louder in this offshoot from the main ```fhallway.  The passageway is much more cramped, but the flurry of ```factivity from the smaller spiderlings is increased.  The smaller ```fcreatures seem to be ferrying food and water to their much, much ```flarger kin working hard to extend the cave complex. ``

`fAs you stumble into the cave entrance you are quickly overwhelmed by a```fstinking fog of chemicals.  The smaller skitterer spiders here seem to```fbe tinted green and even their chitinous armor seems to be mutated.  ```fJust by looking at them you can tell the bite from these arachnids would```fbe very deadly.  While you can hear the sounds of tunneling and the ```foccasional sapper charge go off in these caves, like the others, you also```fcan hear the sounds of bubbling liquids and screaming victims off in the distance.``

`fThe poisonous fog of haze in this cave only gets thicker and thicker as you ```fprogress deeper into the earth.  The spiderkin seem to be immune but it is```fsignificant slowly your progression.  The sounds of laboratory equipment ```fconducting experiments gets louder as do the screams of victims being tested```fon, you only hope you can reach them in time to save them, or to slay them```fand save them from a worse fate.``
